content:
When you want to know sum, average, highest, or lowest value of a numeric column (like Amount, Age, or Probability), summarize the column. Summaries calculate subtotals for every group in a report, as well as a grand total for all report data.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To create, edit, and delete reports:
Enhanced Folder Sharing
Create and Customize Reports
Report Builder

Edit a report. Find the numeric column you'd like to summarize. Click Summarize, and then choose how you'd like to evaluate the data: Sum, Average, Max, Min.

A check mark appears next to already-applied summaries. Each field's type is denoted by an icon directly to the left of the field name. Numeric fields are identified by a number sign (#).

For each group in the report, every summary you apply appears as a subtotal. At the bottom of the report, summaries appear as a total.

Example: After building a basic opportunity report grouped by Stage, summarize the Amount column. Click Summarize, and then choose how you'd like to evaluate the data: Sum, Average, Max, Min.

To add a summary field:
Double-click a number field in the Fields pane.
Drag a number field into the preview.
Choose Summarize this Field in the column menu for a field already in the report.

Reorder sets of summary fields in matrix reports by dragging them. The summaries for each field move together when dragged.

To remove a summary field:
Click its menu and choose Remove Summary.
Drag the summary set back to the Fields pane. All summaries for that field are removed.
title: Summarize Report Data in Salesforce
